Vol / Page:  44
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Maori</i> .... [in] its slightly contemptuous adjectival use, as in <i>a Maori dog, a Maori garden, Maori manners</i>. Here the term is employed to signify something unkempt, rather disordered or wild, something a little `uncivilized'.
Notes:

