Quote:  `Where you from?' ... `Up country. Taranaki say'. `Do you have to make your own tracks to get there?' `Just about.' `Same up home. I'm East Coast.' [218] They kidded each other in a way that would have been offensive with <i>pakehas</i>. When Shirley put a cigarette-butt down the sink ... Netta would say, `That's a real Maori trick, that one! Real East Coast!'
